BALLAST RESISTOR = GENERIC CHRYSLER STYLE (NAPA PART #13 ICR OR EQUIVALENT)
STARTER SOLENOID TO BE 4-TERMINAL FORD STYLE (SEE NOTE #4)

A 3-TERMINAL SOLENOID CAN BE SUBSTITUTED. SIMPLY OMIT THE WIRE BETWEEN
THE "I" TERMINAL AND THE BALLAST RESISTOR
REVERSE CONNECTIONS TO AMMETER IF IT READS "BACKWARD" AFTER CONVERSION
